1
00:00:49,184 --> 00:00:52,768
=In Love With Loving You=
(Based on Love by Erxi on Qimao)

2
00:00:52,768 --> 00:00:55,520
=Episode 11=

3
00:00:57,600 --> 00:00:58,799
Do you have enemies?

4
00:01:00,759 --> 00:01:02,520
No enemies, just creditors.

5
00:01:02,960 --> 00:01:05,319
Have you ever dealt
with something like this before?

6
00:01:06,719 --> 00:01:08,959
I've had paint thrown at me,
locks glued shut.

7
00:01:09,640 --> 00:01:10,799
How much debt is left?

8
00:01:11,079 --> 00:01:12,359
Still 100,000 yuan in debt.

9
00:01:12,719 --> 00:01:15,560
But Mr. Liao gave me 200,000 yuan
for my four years of college.

10
00:01:16,040 --> 00:01:17,920
So altogether, that's 300,000 yuan.

11
00:01:20,120 --> 00:01:21,200
You needn't repay Liao Bei.

12
00:01:22,599 --> 00:01:24,239
I need to. I absolutely must.

13
00:01:24,959 --> 00:01:27,200
I've owed this debt of gratitude
for too many years.

14
00:01:27,200 --> 00:01:29,760
If I don't repay it, I
won't be able to live with myself.

15
00:01:30,359 --> 00:01:33,239
Besides, Mr. Liao is the one
who actually sponsored me.

16
00:01:33,359 --> 00:01:36,640
Isn't it improper for you
to be so generous with others' money?

17
00:01:39,719 --> 00:01:40,359
True.

18
00:02:10,120 --> 00:02:12,159
Mr. Song, you said before

19
00:02:12,159 --> 00:02:14,779
that I'd get a commission if I secured
the Bisheng project.

20
00:02:14,779 --> 00:02:15,599
Is that true?

21
00:02:16,599 --> 00:02:17,560
If you complete it.

22
00:02:18,639 --> 00:02:19,400
I'll work hard.

23
00:02:22,879 --> 00:02:25,960
Why did you choose Wu Rui?

24
00:02:28,039 --> 00:02:28,680
He's reliable.

25
00:02:29,120 --> 00:02:30,960
Scarred by Xiao Jin,

26
00:02:31,360 --> 00:02:32,800
you're now going for the safe type?

27
00:02:36,439 --> 00:02:38,560
Wu Rui's at least
more straightforward than you.

28
00:02:40,479 --> 00:02:43,159
How do you know I'm not straightforward?

29
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:51,000
Mr. Song, I'm done eating.
I'm going to bed first.

30
00:03:14,280 --> 00:03:15,319
Just you wait.

31
00:03:32,039 --> 00:03:33,840
Mr. Song, you go up first.

32
00:03:33,879 --> 00:03:35,520
I'll come up ten minutes after you

33
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:37,240
to prevent misunderstandings.

34
00:03:37,680 --> 00:03:40,400
So you're saying
you'll arrive later than your boss?

35
00:03:41,039 --> 00:03:42,560
Then I'll go up first?

36
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:44,800
You want your boss to wait here for you?

37
00:03:46,479 --> 00:03:47,800
Then what do you suggest?

38
00:03:52,439 --> 00:03:53,400
We'll go up together.

39
00:03:55,560 --> 00:03:56,360
What are you doing?

40
00:03:57,560 --> 00:03:58,360
Mr. Liao?

41
00:04:00,879 --> 00:04:02,319
Why are you two together?

42
00:04:03,199 --> 00:04:05,439
Last night, did you two...

43
00:04:05,919 --> 00:04:07,960
Mr. Song and I just ran into each other.

44
00:04:10,280 --> 00:04:11,080
Let's go upstairs.

45
00:04:24,680 --> 00:04:27,000
Mr. Liao, I made you a cup of coffee.

46
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:29,680
Mr. Liao doesn't like coffee.

47
00:04:31,480 --> 00:04:34,000
Right. I don't like coffee.

48
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:35,079
I even forgot it myself.

49
00:04:35,079 --> 00:04:36,360
Then I'll make you some tea.

50
00:04:36,720 --> 00:04:37,439
Ji Xuan,

51
00:04:37,879 --> 00:04:40,560
the company didn't hire you
to study beverages.

52
00:04:41,079 --> 00:04:41,639
Sit down.

53
00:04:45,759 --> 00:04:47,639
Have you found anything about Mr. Yu?

54
00:04:47,800 --> 00:04:49,480
I asked a friend at the airline.

55
00:04:49,720 --> 00:04:51,319
Mr. Yu lands in Qingcheng
next Wednesday.

56
00:04:51,560 --> 00:04:52,800
But strangely,

57
00:04:52,839 --> 00:04:56,160
starting that day, the beach campsite
is booked exclusively for a month.

58
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:07,519
Mei, this is where I proposed to you.

59
00:05:08,639 --> 00:05:09,879
Revisiting this place,

60
00:05:10,480 --> 00:05:12,439
but now I'm here all alone.

61
00:05:42,720 --> 00:05:43,279
Over there.

62
00:05:49,728 --> 00:05:50,319
Let's go.

63
00:06:01,680 --> 00:06:02,680
Excuse me.

64
00:06:03,160 --> 00:06:04,680
This area is booked exclusively.

65
00:06:08,519 --> 00:06:09,209
Sir,

66
00:06:09,888 --> 00:06:11,759
it's my girlfriend
and my anniversary today.

67
00:06:12,079 --> 00:06:13,279
Mind if we share the area?

68
00:06:15,360 --> 00:06:16,639
Let them in.

69
00:06:16,800 --> 00:06:17,376
Yes.

70
00:06:17,879 --> 00:06:19,000
Please, you two.

71
00:06:43,399 --> 00:06:44,360
Is this cooked?

72
00:06:44,480 --> 00:06:45,279
Not yet, I think.

73
00:06:54,176 --> 00:06:54,720
It's good.

74
00:07:00,319 --> 00:07:00,864
Are you okay?

75
00:07:01,119 --> 00:07:02,120
I got burned.

76
00:07:05,319 --> 00:07:05,959
I'm fine.

77
00:07:36,959 --> 00:07:39,399
Sir, try my girlfriend's cooking.

78
00:07:48,720 --> 00:07:51,120
Mr. Song, you've been acting all along.

79
00:07:51,279 --> 00:07:54,279
Who exactly are you deceiving?
Her or me?

80
00:07:57,680 --> 00:07:59,600
News about you travels far.

81
00:07:59,600 --> 00:08:02,920
Though I'm old, my mind's still sharp.

82
00:08:03,079 --> 00:08:07,079
I clearly remember
Miss Xie was your fiancée.

83
00:08:15,800 --> 00:08:17,839
I've long heard you see and hear all.

84
00:08:17,920 --> 00:08:20,199
Seems nothing escapes you.

85
00:08:20,920 --> 00:08:22,199
I hate beating around the bush.

86
00:08:22,199 --> 00:08:23,920
Get to the point. Why are you here?

87
00:08:25,560 --> 00:08:27,240
She's a project manager at Song Group.

88
00:08:27,959 --> 00:08:30,040
She wants the land you hold.

89
00:08:30,160 --> 00:08:32,080
If that's why you're here,

90
00:08:32,519 --> 00:08:34,120
save your breath.

91
00:08:35,039 --> 00:08:36,759
My late wife bought that land.

92
00:08:37,080 --> 00:08:39,000
I won't sell it under any circumstances.

93
00:08:39,799 --> 00:08:40,679
Go back.

94
00:09:08,080 --> 00:09:08,879
He refuses to sell.

95
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:19,639
It's okay.

96
00:09:20,200 --> 00:09:21,320
We'll find another way.

97
00:09:26,000 --> 00:09:28,840
They say if you know someone's past,

98
00:09:29,080 --> 00:09:30,039
you see their future.

99
00:09:30,679 --> 00:09:32,679
I had someone look into
Mr. Yu's overseas projects.

100
00:09:33,080 --> 00:09:34,200
You may focus on your work.

101
00:10:13,399 --> 00:10:14,120
Any findings?

102
00:10:16,399 --> 00:10:17,720
Mr. Yu is very sentimental.

103
00:10:18,120 --> 00:10:20,480
His whole life revolved around his wife.

104
00:10:21,039 --> 00:10:23,039
They visited countless
art exhibitions together.

105
00:10:23,600 --> 00:10:25,320
They crossed forests, deserts,

106
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:27,720
and the great rivers of many countries.

107
00:10:28,080 --> 00:10:30,559
For such romantic free spirits
like them,

108
00:10:30,759 --> 00:10:33,440
If they bought a plot of land,
what would they do with it?

109
00:10:33,960 --> 00:10:35,519
It's been sitting idle for a long time.

110
00:10:36,080 --> 00:10:37,799
Clearly, it's not for making money.

111
00:10:40,720 --> 00:10:43,440
Mr. Yu met with a famous
overseas art district designer.

112
00:10:43,879 --> 00:10:45,120
If I'm guessing correctly,

113
00:10:45,720 --> 00:10:48,639
he seeks a land designer
but is unsatisfied with the results.

114
00:10:49,080 --> 00:10:50,120
Any ideas?

115
00:10:50,559 --> 00:10:51,480
I think

116
00:10:51,840 --> 00:10:54,519
if we can come up
with a design plan that satisfies him,

117
00:10:55,039 --> 00:10:56,519
we could use that as an opening

118
00:10:56,519 --> 00:10:58,360
to get Mr. Yu to sell us the land.

119
00:10:58,360 --> 00:10:59,080
Good idea.

120
00:11:01,759 --> 00:11:02,720
Have some fruit.

121
00:11:05,399 --> 00:11:06,279
What's with your hand?

122
00:11:10,919 --> 00:11:14,320
I accidentally hurt it
while cutting fruit for you.

123
00:11:15,200 --> 00:11:18,320
You can cook meals,
yet you got hurt cutting fruit?

124
00:11:34,196 --> 00:11:35,988
♪In the vast sea of stars♪

125
00:11:36,148 --> 00:11:38,028
♪Flickering neon lights♪

126
00:11:38,228 --> 00:11:41,556
♪Longing spreads
throughout the universe♪

127
00:11:42,068 --> 00:11:44,340
♪Every star is♪

128
00:11:44,628 --> 00:11:48,500
♪My heartbeat for you♪

129
00:11:49,812 --> 00:11:51,636
♪Want to ride the evening breeze♪

130
00:11:51,796 --> 00:11:53,348
♪And land in your arms♪

131
00:11:53,748 --> 00:11:57,204
♪The starry sky is like your eyes♪

132
00:11:57,460 --> 00:12:00,020
♪In the blue sky♪

133
00:12:00,084 --> 00:12:04,212
♪Your smile still lingers♪

134
00:12:05,140 --> 00:12:08,788
♪You are the brightest light
in my regrets♪

135
00:12:09,044 --> 00:12:12,708
♪You are the painful greeting
in my despair♪

136
00:12:12,916 --> 00:12:15,828
♪Can't find a cure♪

137
00:12:15,828 --> 00:12:20,340
♪To love you after we've parted♪

138
00:12:20,532 --> 00:12:24,564
♪You are the time I most want to keep♪

139
00:12:24,564 --> 00:12:28,428
♪The future I strive toward
in the darkness♪

140
00:12:28,428 --> 00:12:30,228
♪Slowly getting closer to you♪

141
00:12:30,324 --> 00:12:35,476
♪How I wish
I could give you my sunshine♪

142
00:12:36,116 --> 00:12:39,828
♪You are the brightest light
in my regrets♪

143
00:12:40,020 --> 00:12:42,772
♪Can't find a cure♪

144
00:12:42,900 --> 00:12:47,540
♪To love you after we've parted♪

145
00:12:47,708 --> 00:12:51,476
♪You are the time I most want to keep♪

146
00:12:51,700 --> 00:12:55,284
♪The future I strive toward
in the darkness♪

147
00:12:55,508 --> 00:12:57,408
♪Slowly getting closer to you♪

148
00:12:57,408 --> 00:13:02,548
♪How I wish
I could give you my sunshine♪
